{
  "id": "q-zk-host-functions-status",
  "question": "Which zero-knowledge cryptographic host functions are live on Stellar as of July 2026, which CAPs introduced them, and what gaps remain for STARK-style verification?",
  "surface": [
    "skills.stellar-dev.zk-proofs",
    "skills.stellar-dev.standards",
    "stellarDocs.search_protocol_concepts_docs"
  ],
  "golden": {
    "answer": "As of 2026-07-11, CAP-0059's BLS12-381 host functions (Protocol 22), CAP-0074's BN254 and CAP-0075's Poseidon/Poseidon2 primitives (Protocol 25), and CAP-0080's BN254 MSM, scalar-field arithmetic, inversion, and curve-membership checks (Protocol 26) are live: pubnet and testnet reported Protocol 27. These are low-level primitives, not complete proof systems. There were no documented native Goldilocks, NTT, or FRI host functions as of that date, so STARK-style verifiers need additional Wasm work or another architecture.",
    "keyFacts": [
      "CAP-0059 introduced BLS12-381 host functions with minimum supported Protocol 22.",
      "Protocol 25 added BN254 via Final CAP-0074 and Poseidon/Poseidon2 via Final CAP-0075.",
      "Protocol 26 implemented Final CAP-0080, adding BN254 MSM, scalar-field add/subtract/multiply/power/inverse, and curve-membership checks.",
      "Pubnet and testnet reported Protocol 27 on 2026-07-11, so the Protocol 22, 25, and 26 primitives were live there.",
      "There were no documented native Goldilocks, NTT, or FRI host functions as of 2026-07-11."
    ],
    "avoid": [
      "CAP-0074 and CAP-0075 are still merely proposed and unavailable on mainnet as of July 2026.",
      "Native ZK host functions are complete end-to-end proof systems."
    ],
    "notes": "Status-sensitive details are stated as of 2026-07-11; grade later sourced changes leniently and require dated primary evidence."
  },
